# Serena MCP

Use Serena for symbol-level code inspection before modifying unfamiliar code.

Use for unfamiliar modules, refactors, tracing call sites, and surgical symbol edits.

Start: `initial_instructions` once per session, then `activate_project` if needed.

Inspect: `get_symbols_overview`, `find_symbol`, `find_declaration`, `find_referencing_symbols`, `find_implementations`.

Edit only when appropriate: `replace_symbol_body`, `rename_symbol`, `insert_before_symbol`, `insert_after_symbol`.

Use cocoindex-code or repo search for broad discovery; use Serena for precise symbol work.

